6708448.name: Assignment 1
6708448.description: The first Matlab assignment is due Friday February 16, 2024 at 11:59 PM (Maryland time) on Gradescope. You may work with up to 2 other people ( groups of 3 ) and submit one PDF on Gradescope. Make sure to add ALL NAMES TO YOUR GROUP when you submit 1 file on Gradescope.  THERE SHOULD BE AN OPTION TO "ADD GROUP MEMBERS."  MAKE SURE TO MARK THE PAGES. Matlab can be downloaded for free here: https://terpware.umd.edu/Windows/Title/1849 Basic instructions on using Matlab can be found here: MATLAB_basics.pdf A simple template you can start your assignment with, and Publish to see the correct formatting: Example_Matlab_File.m A sample output of what your file should look like: Example_Matlab_File_Output.pdf A simple tutorial to upload to Gradescope and HOW TO MARK YOUR PAGES: Gradescope_tutorial.mp4 Assignment1_S24.pdf

5357635.title: Exam 3 Info (5/1)
5357635.message: Exam 3 will be WEDNESDAY May 1 during the usual class time (1-1:50 PM).  NO CALCULATORS or any external devices can be used. The rooms will be split up like exam 1 and 2. If you are in Sections 311 or 321 (TA is Shenghao) , you will take the exam in ESJ 2208 . As the exam will state, if you are in the wrong room for the exam, 5 points will be deducted from your exam score. All other sections will take the exam in the regular classroom (ESJ 0202) The exam will cover up to and including Section 6.5, Least Squares Problems.  (The main focus begins on Section 5.1, 5.2: Eigenvectors and Eigenvalues, and The Characteristic Equation).
